      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and prove the dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the flour, sugar, salt, and yeast. Add the evaporated milk, water, egg, and melted butter and mix until a soft, cohesive dough forms. Knead for 5 to 7 minutes until smooth. The dough will be slightly sticky, resist adding more flour. Place in an oiled bowl, cover, and prove for 1 hour until doubled.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cut and fry",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oil to 180°C. On a lightly floured surface, roll the proved dough to 5 mm thick. Cut into 6 to 7 cm squares. Do not prove again after cutting, the beignets go straight into the oil. Fry 3 to 4 at a time for 45 to 60 seconds per side. They will puff dramatically and may flip themselves; help any that haven't turned by gently nudging them. Fry until pale gold on both sides. Drain briefly on the rack, then dust immediately and heavily with icing sugar.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
